Date:  0/0/1855
Source:  Te ika a Maui
Author:  TAYLOR
Vol / Page:  414
Edition:
Quote:  Amongst the Crustacea is the <i>koura</i>, which is the general name for both the sea cray fish and the fresh water; the former is nearly two feet long, and abundant on all the rocky shores; the latter is from four to eight inches long. The Rotorua lakes abound with the largest, but near Paparoa, on the Wanganui, i met with one nearly a foot long.
