Date:  0/0/1898
Source:  Austral English
Author:  MORRiS
Vol / Page:  254
Edition:
Quote:  <i>Kowhai, n.</i> Maori name given to (i) Locust-tree, <i>Yellow Kowhai (Sophora tetraptera</i>, Aiton, N.O. <i>Leguminosae</i>). (2) Parrot-bill, <i>Scarlet Kowhai ( Clianthus puniceus, N.O. Leguminosae</i>, or <i>Kaka-bill</i>. (q.v.). Variously spelt <i>kowai</i> and <i>kohai</i>, and corrupted into Goai(q.v.). by the settlers.
Notes:

